Installing a module.
$  npm install <package name>

Uninstalling a module 
npm uninstall module_name.

Global mode.
npm install -g sax
In this mode packages will be installed in 


Installing a particular version of a package.

$  npm install <package name>@<version spec>
$  npm install sax@0.2.5



Updating installed modules.

$  npm update <module name>

Resolving Dependencies.
For each file note that Npm also checks for dependecies in package.json and installs the dependencies of those files.

npm update <package name>

To globally update modules do this.
npm update -g <package name>